cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the issues related to Mobile Ad Hoc Networks (MANETs) and proposes an improved protocol for better performance. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper also discusses the security issues in MANETs and proposes a solution to overcome them. This falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the distributed nature of MANETs and proposes a protocol for better performance. This falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes an improved protocol for MANETs, which involves the use of algorithms. This falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the communication and connectivity between nodes in MANETs, which falls under the scope of social and information networks.
